mation. So too is the fact that organizational change happens one individual at a time. For transformation to take root, each person must shift his or her sense of self at work and the role that he or she plays in the transforming organization. Intended as a road map, rather than a "how-to" manual with fixed procedures, Organizational Transformation will help leaders to locate their organization's position on a continuum of progress and confidently navigate planned, whole-systems change, overcoming the challenges of growing from and adjusting to watershed moments.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aOrganizational changexManagement. 4aidentity. 4aleadership development. 4aleadership. 4aorganizational change. 4aownership. 4aself-concept. 4astates. 4atransformation. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Organizational Behavior.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311070368940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360584840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503605848423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503605848.jpg  a978-3-11-070368-9  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles